                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Gado-gado is a traditional Indonesian salad renowned for its vibrant flavors and colorful presentation. 
                    This beloved dish features a delightful medley of blanched vegetables, such as potatoes, string beans, 
                    and cabbage, combined with tofu, tempeh, and hard-boiled eggs, creating a satisfying array of textures. 
                    The salad is then generously dressed with a creamy and aromatic peanut sauce, made from roasted peanuts, 
                    garlic, chili, palm sugar, and tamarind juice, offering a perfect balance of sweetness, tanginess, and 
                    spiciness. Gado-gado is often garnished with crispy fried shallots and emping crackers, adding a delightful 
                    crunch to every bite. As a versatile and nutritious dish, gado-gado is enjoyed throughout Indonesia as a 
                    hearty meal or appetizing snack, cherished for its rich flavors and wholesome ingredients.
                </p>
